---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Affiliate Disclosure | The Lawn Guide"
  description="How The Lawn Guide makes money, and why that matters for the recommendations you read here."
>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 md:py-20">
    <header class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-terracotta-600 font-medium mb-4">Disclosure</p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl text-forest-900 leading-tight tracking-tight">
        How this site is funded
      </h1>
    </header>

    <div class="prose">
      <p class="text-xl text-ink-700 leading-relaxed mb-8 font-serif italic">
        The Lawn Guide is funded by affiliate commissions. This page explains exactly what that means and how it affects what you read here.
      </p>

      <h2>What is an affiliate link?</h2>
      <p>
        Many of the product links on this site are affiliate links. When you click one and go on to buy something from the retailer, I earn a small commission on the sale. The price you pay is exactly the same whether you use my link or go to the retailer directly.
      </p>
      <p>
        I work with retailers and affiliate networks including Amazon Associates UK, Awin, Commission Junction (CJ), and direct programmes with UK lawn care brands. Specific retailers I may earn commission from include Amazon, Crocus, Gardening Naturally, You Garden, Thompson & Morgan, MOOWY, The Grass People, and Lawnsmith, among others.
      </p>

      <h2>How this affects what I recommend</h2>
      <p>
        It doesn't, and I'm honest about why. A bad recommendation breaks reader trust. A site that recommends rubbish products to chase higher commission rates loses its audience within months. The whole business model depends on you finding the recommendations useful enough that you come back.
      </p>
      <p>
        So I only recommend products I'd genuinely use on my own lawn. If a higher-commission product is worse than a lower-commission one, I recommend the lower-commission one. If something I've reviewed positively turns out to be a dud after longer-term use, I update or remove the article.
      </p>

      <h2>What I don't do</h2>
      <p>
        I don't take payment for positive reviews. I don't accept "sponsored content" disguised as editorial. I don't link to products I haven't either used personally or assessed in detail against alternatives. I don't write reviews of products I haven't seen.
      </p>
      <p>
        If a brand sends me a product to review, I'll say so clearly in the article. Receiving a product to test does not guarantee a positive review.
      </p>

      <h2>Disclosure on individual articles</h2>
      <p>
        Every article that contains affiliate links carries a disclosure notice near the top. This is required under UK Advertising Standards Authority (ASA) and Competition and Markets Authority (CMA) guidelines, and I take it seriously regardless of the regulation.
      </p>

      <h2>Questions</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any questions about how this site is funded, how I choose what to review, or anything else, email me at <a href="mailto:hello@lawnguide.co.uk">hello@lawnguide.co.uk</a>.
      </p>

      <p class="text-sm text-ink-500 mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-forest-200/60">
        Last updated: May 2026
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>